    "## What the figure shows\n",
    "\n",
    "Detrital-zircon sample paleo-positions at `RECONSTRUCTION_TIME` Ma on a paleo-Earth map, split into two colour-coded sub-populations:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **\"Near subduction\"** \u2014 samples whose paleo-distance to the nearest contemporaneous trench is below `DISTANCE_THRESHOLD_KM`. These zircons are interpreted as having a continental-arc / convergent-margin tectonic source.\n",
    "- **\"Far from subduction\"** \u2014 samples beyond the threshold. These are interpreted as intracratonic / passive-margin source, distinct from arc volcanism.\n",
    "\n",
    "The hypothesis under test (after Jian, Williams, Yu & Zhao 2022) is that the U\u2013Pb age signature of detrital zircons reflects the tectonic setting in which they were deposited. The split shown here is the spatial step in that classification \u2014 a follow-up histogram of U\u2013Pb ages, faceted by the near/far split, would surface the signature differences. The number of samples in each class is printed below the map.\n"
   ]
